The river flows, a silver thread,  
Through valleys deep and wide;  
In its reflection, dreams are spread,  
And secrets of the tide;  
The mountains high in glory rise,  
Guarding Nature’s sacred gate,  
While beneath the vast, unending skies,  
Life weaves a tale of fate.

- Isaac Rosenberg
